               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240603-213-person1817">
                  JOHN 
                  WALES
               <interp inst="t18240603-213-person1817" type="surname" value="WALES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-213-person1817" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-213-person1817" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer, and was in Piccadilly on the 23d of April; about three o'clock in the afternoon I saw the two prisoners on the opposite side of the way in conversation with each other. Low had something on his shoulder; from their manner I suspected something wrong; they went into the Green-park, and when they came to one of the benches they laid it down to rest; I went up and turned up the corner of the canvass and said,</p>
               <p>"What have you got here?" It was about 80 lbs. of lead; they made no reply; I took them into custody, and put them in the watch-house, and then went down Piccadilly and saw Condon, who went with me to the watch-house and saw the lead.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240603-213-person1818">
                  WILLIAM 
                  CONDON
               <interp inst="t18240603-213-person1818" type="surname" value="CONDON"></interp>
